<p>I want a link to appear within a twitter tweet. At the moment the raw HTML comes out. </p>  <pre><code>click &lt;a href=\"www.google.com\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; to test </code></pre>  <p>Here is my code.</p>  <pre><code>$url = 'www.google.com' $text = urlencode( "click &lt;a href=\"www.google.com\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; to test" )  $share   = 'http://twitter.com/share'; $url     = '?url=' . $url; $text    = '&amp;text=' . $title; $hashtag = '&amp;hashtags=' . $hashtag; $url     = $share . $url . $text . $hashtag; </code></pre>  <p>Without <code>urlencode()</code> the actual twitter icon then spits out HTML text everywhere on my page.</p>